# Pull Request Style

PR title = conventional commit. PR body must include:

```
## Brief
.cursor/subagent-briefs/<NN-stream>.md

## What & why
<short>

## Acceptance criteria
- [ ] criterion 1
- [ ] criterion 2

## Evals
Paste promptfoo/DeepEval summary or "n/a" with reason.

## Screenshots / GIFs
For UI changes.

## Risk / rollback
How to roll back if needed.
```

- Run the `review-bugbot` skill on every PR.
- Run `review-security` on PRs touching: `auth`, `memory`, `graphrag`, `mcp`, RBAC, encryption, payments.
- Prefer many small PRs (use the `split-to-prs` skill) over giant ones.
- Do not merge your own PR if any reviewer requested changes and they're unresolved.
